  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Peel and chop your<strong> sweet potato[es]</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Chop your <strong>potato[es]</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/german-style-curried-sausage-tray-bake/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and chop <strong>half</strong> your <strong>red onion[s]</strong> into wedges (you'll use the rest later!)</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/german-style-curried-sausage-tray-bake/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>sausages</strong>, <strong>chopped potato</strong>, <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>sweet potato </strong>and<strong> onion wedges </strong>to a baking tray (or two!) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a generous grind of <strong>black</strong> <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 25-30 min or until the sausages are cooked through (no pink meat!) and the potatoes are golden</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/german-style-curried-sausage-tray-bake/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>While everything is in the oven, finely dice the <strong>remaining red onion</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>shredded kale</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/german-style-curried-sausage-tray-bake/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until softened</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic </strong>and cook for a further 1-2 min</p><p>Once everything has softened, add most of your <strong>curry powder</strong> (save a little for garnish!) and <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong> and cook for 30 secs</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/german-style-curried-sausage-tray-bake/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>tomato paste</strong>,<strong> Henderson's Relish</strong>,<strong> tomato ketchup </strong>and<strong> </strong>200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[340ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> to the pan</p><p>Give everything a good mix up and cook for 3-4 min or until the sauce has reduced to a thick gravy-like consistency – this is your<strong> curried tomato sauce</strong></p><p>Once thickened, remove the pan from the heat and set aside</p><p>Warm through again just before serving</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/german-style-curried-sausage-tray-bake/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> to your <strong>shredded</strong> <strong>kale</strong> and massage it with clean hands so that it's evenly covered in oil</p><p>Once the sausages are cooked, remove the tray[s] from the oven and sprinkle over the <strong>shredded kale</strong></p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven for a further 3-4 min or until the kale is cooked and slightly crispy – this is your <strong>sausage</strong> <strong>tray bake</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/german-style-curried-sausage-tray-bake/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>sausage</strong> <strong>tray bake</strong> with the<strong> curried tomato sauce</strong> drizzled all over</p><p>Sprinkle over the <strong>remaining curry powder</strong> – this is your <strong>German-style curried sausage tray bake</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
